Steps: 

Go to stytch.com and sign up.
Grab a project ID and secret from settings and put them in a .env file as STYTCH_PROJECT_ID and STYTCH_SECRET

Run -
python app.py


Explanation:

We don't want just anyone registering their device in our app. There should be a login feature to ensure it's a trusted user. Here we use Stytch, an Authentication-as-a-Service provider, to set up magic links and SMS OTPs.
The actual site isn't really set up for this example, but it's easy to imagine combining it with example 3 or 4.